title: Biden still not announcing his decision, but taking jabs at those were just secretary of state
text: Vice President Biden used a 50-minute appearance Tuesday to burnish his credentials as President Obama's closest foreign policy adviser, describing his role as more critical than that of the secretary of state, even as he anguishes over whether to enter the 2016 campaign against the nation's former top diplomat, Hillary Rodham Clinton.
